-- Perella Weinberg Partners Hires Ex-Morgan Stanley Investment Banker Durkee
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   R .   M i d e r
-- 2010-10-19T13:52:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/perella-weinberg-partners-hires-ex-morgan-stanley-investment-banker-durkee.html
Perella Weinberg Partners LP hired
 G. Malpass Durkee , a former Morgan Stanley and Merrill Lynch &
Co. investment banker, to advise banks and other financial-
services companies.  Durkee joined as a partner in New York, Perella Weinberg
said in a statement today. He left Morgan Stanley last year
after serving as co-head of the group that advises banks in
North America.  At Merrill Lynch, where Durkee worked from 1995 to 2008, he
advised SouthTrust Corp. on its sale to Wachovia Corp. in 2004
and Regions Financial Corp. on its takeover of AmSouth Bancorp
in 2006. Merrill Lynch was sold to  Bank of America Corp . last
year.  Joseph Perella , a former Morgan Stanley banker, and  Peter Weinberg,  a former Goldman Sachs Group Inc. partner, founded
their New York-based firm in 2006. Its bankers are working on
$56 billion of mergers this year, making it the 22nd-biggest
adviser, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Goldman Sachs
and Morgan Stanley hold the top two spots.  To contact the reporter on this story:
